  "body": "_Github issues are primarily for reporting bugs or getting assistance with development-related items. If you have a question or need support with our product, please email support@mycrypto.com for faster attention._\r\n\r\n_If you are reporting an issue, please use the template below so we can reproduce, determine the cause of the issue, and fix it! If you are not reporting an issue, delete this entire thing and type away. Thanks!_\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n### Description of Issue\r\n\r\nError `Trying to send an incompatible EIP-155 transaction, signed for another chain.` happened when I tried to send ETH from one account to another on a localhost hardhat network.\r\n\r\n### What exactly were you doing when you encountered this issue?\r\n\r\nGiven the following hardhard config file.\r\n```\r\n/**\r\n * @type import('hardhat/config').HardhatUserConfig\r\n */\r\nmodule.exports = {\r\n  solidity: \"0.8.4\",\r\n  networks: {\r\n    hardhat: {\r\n      chainId: 31337\r\n    },\r\n  },\r\n};\r\n```\r\nExecute the local node listening process\r\n```\r\n$ hardhat --config hardhat.config.local.js node\r\nStarted HTTP and WebSocket JSON-RPC server at http://127.0.0.1:8545/`\r\n```\r\n\r\n### How were you accessing your wallet?\r\n\r\nRestoration of generated private keys by hardhat in MyCrypto wallet. Mycrypto wallet is connected to local node.\r\n\r\n### Description of Your Machine\r\n\r\n- Browser:\r\n- Browser version:\r\n- Operating system: Windows 10\r\n- Device: Desktop\r\n- MyCrypto.com vs Desktop Application?\r\n- MyCrypto Version Number: 1.7.17\r\n\r\n### Console Logs / Screenshots\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3234559/134795054-e4f5d391-3d32-4d6d-a1ec-468ec58f231f.png)\r\n\r\n",
